cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper discusses the problem of automatically extracting keyphrases from text, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses supervised learning algorithms, such as decision tree induction and GenEx, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting cs.LG and cs.AI as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions using deep learning (DL) techniques in future work, indicating cs.DL as a possible sub-category.
